description.narrative: Communities are able to hold duty bearers accountable for the delivery of quality and resilient, child-friendly services., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Health, Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys grow up in resilient, inclusive and child friendly communities, that are supported by enabling environment and systems that provide an equitable chance in life.

description.narrative: In partnership with the GoM, local and international NGOs, UNICEF is supporting and strengthening other stakeholders' efforts to establish robust communication channels, feedback loops, referral pathways and complaints feedback mechanisms for all sectors, that are known and accessible to vulnerable communities and individuals.
